[{"Name":"Rieke Indriyanti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNh0kI7VJH7WaJZt9-C1SDxnQRuk6pZlFfzYsSq-P9wudmxU_nsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this hidden gem of a Thai restaurant so much! They have many yummy Thai food menu selections. My favorites are the veggie spring rolls, fried rice, and their pad Thai. The restaurant is very clean with a cozy atmosphere, and the service is fast here. Furthermore, I love the one server who wear their traditional Thai wardrobes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKxdl-jF62LTBm4la3GP5NT6A2fWuT9xR8DbeW&fid=0x0:0x65f91ec66f537890"],"When":"2024-9-4"},{"Name":"Alicia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpuZWTnHlirHopFvIk3V7SKbKzRsJSiN19V2QlgRAnhsf5BR8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We’re so glad we found this gem! The food is amazing and is no different from the great food we had in Thailand. The place isn’t huge but it is tidy. We felt that service is great and price is also fair. Only thing is portion sizes are a bit on the small side and wait times are slightly long when it’s busy, but the food is worth it. Highly recommend!

We had the Bangkok wings, green curry, pad Thai, and mango sticky rice as dessert. Would at least say these didn’t disappoint!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPASHWm2ctes54TamxBVa9lT9tkGJMfUZJiHF_8&fid=0x0:0x65f91ec66f537890"],"When":"2023-6-30"},{"Name":"Angie Novakowski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIafHDJGEfjl7Fqg-4-NXZB9rc26laN7cMbwC5V9Gix5FE-g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Happened to be in White Rock tonight unexpectedly. Googled Thai food/ decided to check it out! Amazing, delicious, authentic, well presented! Our server was very professional & knowledgeable. We had the pineapple red chicken curry... delicious! The chicken pad sew yu was very good as well! We also had the Tom Yum soup; richly seasoned & very fragrant. The next time we're in the area again, we will definitely head over to Leela Thai for another wonderful meal!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Greg Newman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4wy0IFIOFBoK8D8OddsLS_8pyWCN0lN2RRPLB5-ts35zKEg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Wonderfully delicious food and friendly service. Had the green curry and spring rolls. Curry was amazing, a nice punch of spicy. The restaurant could use a splash of paint; liked the wall art.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIr_X0Ngc6uSA0DkvTLlL1X0hyWAj1uDQ6ptiP&fid=0x0:0x65f91ec66f537890"],"When":"2023-8-7"},{"Name":"Jackie Pearce","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLfqAno7eFyGKlwdCsezSbULhY_hu_i939duZ379_z1DUaBL11=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent vegan and gluten free options. Well marked on the menu.

Food was absolutely delicious! No fishy taste in the fried tofu, so I fee like they have two fryers (not sure).

Best Thai I've had in well over a decade.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7ZNNdMnQMm6q7BYyTZAsw7mPK3a-bo1droVn-&fid=0x0:0x65f91ec66f537890"],"When":"2021-7-10"},{"Name":"DAVID GUALDRON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBXhAVJJUe5WhCUkVmO94PWjpULG5Kxv3rXzLTdKp2GVHjI2Cgsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant is nothing pretentious, but is clean, and most important the food is fantastic. The rice tastes delicious, and the best fried banana I've ever tried! . Customer Service is nice, bathrooms are very clean and good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOB2O-dBRK1j_R6aEnk299bJ3GXgyE7LUMzci8K&fid=0x0:0x65f91ec66f537890"],"When":"2017-6-4"},{"Name":"Veronica Chase","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrc1_liOnPkWYfhPrFoOl5MYMgw_8Ti_LXSxJGA9JfbuMLOEuv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"!!!OPEN!!!

Cozy new location. Been going there for 10+ years and still hands down the best this food I have eating around the lower mainland and Vancouver. Family operated and friendly staff. Come hungry 😋 great portions!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPB8Bj-8gvjZ9zRmL_otFweThuHQK5dJ2TOIdBt&fid=0x0:0x65f91ec66f537890"],"When":"2021-2-21"},{"Name":"Leonard Gareau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqXRA_tm_swOWEUNzW7x72QxQ0Y8S-WaTFLVnw2RDqkrtbUCA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This was surprisingly Poor.   Possibly the worst Pad Thai I’ve ever had.  Almost 100% sure the sauce that came with the Veggie Tofu dish came out of a Heinz jar.   Will not be ordering from here again.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Tara Walker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKW1kTu76JveMo2p9nMhdKdTyIKHMDbXw1p-Yhzvh6-6nrVrg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our book club meeting here and absolutely loved this restaurant. We were a half and hour early for our reservation however they accommodated us and we were sat quickly. Our server was a smiley delight. Our meals were fresh and delicious. Highly recommend the pineapple coconut margaritas. Will definitely return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLFKxITIDw6c9iZGOEfdh2Fb3MZbb6j7B_4jB2&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"A Davalovsky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV9HGGyp19V1u4ltzIo94134NhNu-jV70fCbCo-i7ix1jvlI75w5A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Our visit to WAG was very nice, the first time here for us. Our cousin recommended it and we went with them and took another cousin visiting from Ontario. 6 people in total, and everyone was happy with their orders. The only minor complaint was the yam fries appetizer. They were very limp, clumped, and stuck together,  but still were tasty. The decor had a theme, best described as vintage, and then changed on the covered deck. The view was nice, but there was a large parking area between the building and the actual view. The server was pleasant and attentive. She took our orders in a timely manner, and the food arrived reasonably quick and hot. It wasn't very busy, so I can not comment on how things would be if it were busy. Overall, I would definitely recommend it, and we will be back to give it a try again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOM4yDWqrtDcJcoZh7-DzknF64SYMxv0qs-Uizb&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Washington Avenue Grill, or WAG, is an antiquated looking, yet very unique restaurant that is off the corner of the White Rock   business district. I was immediately captivated by its old-fashioned decor. The restaurant is also very spacious and has three dining areas, two of which have great views outside while the one is really clean and elegant looking. I ordered the Pecan Crusted Steelhead with a Bubbly Sangria Mocktail. The sangria I had was testament that you can have a great drink without alcohol. The entree was fantastic. The steelhead tasted good and very meaty. The tarragon sauce was flavourful, and it complimented everything on the dish. Even the vegetables tasted great from how they were seasoned. I liked the staff that were taking care of me, and they looked like they enjoy their work there. If I came back to White Rock, I would make sure to come eat at Washington Avenue again because there are a lot of distinct menu choices that I would like to try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVTsDz0flnRcAqYX7u7FIPCMrP1uIUetefgsOU&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Aaron Maass","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFzA1W2tvNy4XapnycM8nPtO342-bhsuJFoTV6stA5hXKYkKOaHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great decor and service. The food was solid but both their Seafood Hot Pot & Curry Shrimp were a bit too sweet and lacking in spice. It'd be great if they could add additional levels of spice as an option for those dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuTIHWiKwzMuKiu7OUXE0Od5gRb8GcmMjIKGVX&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Christine Diamond","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0GRE4DQDnyjK83r6U_hiPWjq0IAjkCNe52neUjT-g9JA7F9Zc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love it here. We usually get the stuffed Chicken dish, this time we also ordered the Braised Short Ribs. Chicken remains our favourite but the beef was tender and tasty. I prefer a traditional type gravy opposed to the hoisin flavour. But that’s just preference. I asked for bread and balsamic oil dip even though it wasn’t on the menu but I had seen a picture online. That was served to me no problem. The servers are always wonderful here. I got a window table and it was an extra beautiful. It was a Monday and very busy, a testament to this restaurants popularity. There was no front free lot parking so I did have to pay for parking in the back lot, however, there was lots of parking and it was only $5. Better than most other beach front restaurant parking options. And I have gotten free parking 80% of the time, so I certainly cannot complain!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCTxyrDocTg2jdHE11yRtSdwQqAAUnXQBluueq&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food was ok. Not bad but not spectacular. One part of the restaurant looks nice while the other half looks dark and dated…a bit mismatched. Service was ok, but they advertised drink specials on the table that weren’t honoured when it came to pay the bill despite pointing this out to the server. She simply indicated “that’s an old drink special” even though she was the one who pointed out that we should review the drink specials per the drink menu on the table when she seated us. We felt scammed. This is disappointing despite the positive reviews on Google. Not sure we would come back to give it another chance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOte-OzRhUOi-BUrQCtkko-IyXaGCr431-RLN5J&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Omar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLa_FRdIoYzK5bFT5ehOjOH0vLg6K7zbGjBKDG0V29TBwc3hg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our Christmas party at Washington Avenue Grill in White Rock, BC, was an unforgettable experience, and not just because of the amazing food and top-notch service.

There was a power outage right before our event, and we were worried it might force us to reschedule or find another venue. But the incredible team at WAG went above and beyond, setting up generators to ensure everything went smoothly. Not a single beat was skipped!

The food was absolutely delicious, and the staff were attentive, professional, and genuinely cared about making our evening special.

Thank you to the entire WAG team for going the extra mile and making us feel so valued. You turned what could have been a stressful situation into a flawless celebration. Highly recommend this place to anyone planning a special event!  Thank you from your new friend's at Langley Subaru.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL38zrthQPvNvYIAO5hkWxK7ISAVwNkml8z06BB9pJtb1L0Dg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Loved the food and the atmosphere. The waitress was friendly and hospitable. The ocean view was remarkable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTtR0dFias0JyD-_ooDQ40TGyUYuZ5hZ1zsUIw&fid=0x0:0xbe2b53c7d35ebd98"],"When":"2024-9-8"}]

[{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very cute Italian restaurant with some delicious pasta! The owners are super friendly people, and they serve some very tasty dishes. This is a great place to go from a nice dinner or just some very good seafood pasta! I also highly recommend their Baia sunset cocktail :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeNwW2-7r0rOjLjfyv_WFU-AhgBaJgc9NcjWdK&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Ane Strathdee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOlZ1L6DU41aUczU482PdKoXEm0OeL0U4SjOs7WWki0ZC9Hkuu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We’ve come here many times. David was our server before and he is fantastic! Tracy was our server this time and she was great, very helpful and professional. Dishes were good, the bottle of wine we’ve ordered was perfect! Tracy recommend it, and it was a hit. Looking forward to coming back again. Thanks to the whole staff and the owner for the warm welcome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkbe91ZYnib4jls9ldlTgwyz4bEvugkCr9O8wg&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2023-6-18"},{"Name":"David Low","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkpc3i0EhqNBPlJnkSMEHMpro396LQMF6uOQ9XPiyoabidlekP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great restaurant with good variety. Went on Mothers Day and their menu was a smaller but still good! Their pastas are still great and I highly recommend the lasagnas! Very filling so bring an appetite. Also parking is very limited on a Sunday lunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDDbriDvHOz4raxmo3zbCdq05UW0-CRt7KnTqp&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2023-5-14"},{"Name":"Kat G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVeugpopU5QOP13cYsLu7XQv9XmCvvghtYGIrRHN-IrSnLsA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So glad we found this local cute little place that was open at the time we needed lunch (12pm) before flying back to the states.

Food is great, everyone love the dish they ordered.  Quality Italian food.  Tracie is super nice, not rushing, relaxing and created a great atmosphere experience for us.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDeD2AxU3LjRMrHkm_5Wp-B7sEprBfzIRpilgP&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2023-6-3"},{"Name":"Liz Kitura","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXp89k0W4BukjgygkT9TfQtqMs-pWbqIa1J4s3xVyQuCKAbBe_a=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had dinner here with a couple friends. There is a 20% off pasta special on Wednesday, and I was looking forward to trying out the menu.

The portions were pretty small for the price to be honest, even with the discount, and I was left feeling hungry after my pasta when I usually have a pretty small appetite. My husband didn't really care for his gnocchi, the texture was fine but the sauce tasted like it was from a jar. The linguine vongole was pretty good, but the flavour of the thin sauce didn't really stick to the noodles that much so most of it ended up on the bottom of the bowl. The linguine with meatballs was devoured by my friends, and they were left feeling very full and happy with their order. The desserts were pretty good.

The service was great however, and it's in a really good location to walk the beach before or after.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZIBuO_W6fY5r1tldE4htabI2ZEo5e0XC9O6jb&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2022-7-7"},{"Name":"Timothy Chan (TimTim)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURIoSl-5oBZzcRd91bCuWm5mXoW-rsGa8ZawpNSjddYI4bCo-k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"La Baia means ‘the bay’, a name befitting to this family friendly Italian restaurant with a fine dining vibe, right by the bay in White Rock. Food and service are both excellent. Also has live piano music played by young pianists. Truly a great little getaway restaurant away from the busy Vancouver life!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQsOn3Ogh1uut8EECXK6oBvQKWShGzux-gP70M&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2023-7-23"},{"Name":"Darren Chua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_RDoSvjggyY_Qo2KMO4Ma5AoX001jw_--XBGhuAaBOILSKTGO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall a pleasant experience with great food and service. I found it a bit odd that they charge separately between $1-$3 for the kind of pasta preferred with no default option.

Nonetheless, decent sized portions and a nice ambience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCc2eRPVztp4mKEHzOu8WRixUu8mCNVPkxw_pM&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2024-3-29"},{"Name":"Rachel Blades","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6TxtTSw9EN02Nkikl9w8FBVT6r66iRiWy7vu8WprpnuX5vqAx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had dinner here last night for the first time. The food was phenomenal! I was originally going to choose the seafood canelloni but our server suggested the daily special-the seafood lasagna-so I ordered that. It was SO DELICIOUS. We also ordered the meat lasagna and cheese toast, both were amazing. The pasta dishes had so many delicious cheeses and the flavours were fresh and exquisite. Highly recommend this place and we will be back!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP65i1xPxmmHXjeM8uNrspUb8O3ckK1xDSuPyXp&fid=0x0:0x2759b3c5cda117cd"],"When":"2022-12-11"}]

[{"Name":"Foodieatlarge Ou812!","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV5WjUsogcvFcdpk650G44_1nDSsUxfDfJjUXorbWVcHcaIaXI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been over 10 yrs since last review at PG's Jamaican Restaurant and it still remains an authentic choice for sublime Jamaican fare.
Love the Curried GOAT so much, pure comfort food with simple  ingredients simmered to perfection under the watchful eye of an experienced chef. This GOAT is so well prepared with the savoury richness only goat can deliver without the foul odor or rank flavour if not spiced and simmered correctly. Reminiscent  of Rehanahas goat in Coquitlam which is equally delicious too!
If u have never tried goat and u enjoy rich, deep flavours with a wee bit o spice go eat at PG's or Rehanas.
Both authentic Jamaican mon.
Both staffed by warm,genuine ppl who want to feed u well.
U will seriously wanna lick the plate at P.G's Jamaican Restaurant!

Go Mon, go now Mon!
Appy Trails kids,
Brianm
Foodieatlarge.OU812","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsBaYElN_MX7LdLf8MzKK2KuQn4Dp-3gCXwvd0&fid=0x0:0x79a44c577165f939"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Sarah A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVNn7Y9x948-EY0euJdBSiyjyAPiAJZZI4ZzDyvxd_bfYEHlvz5QQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food and service. I ordered the jerk chicken plate and beef patties. Everything was super yummy and the chef came out to say hi. Definitely make a stop here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSyzBeRzLvD8UcBr4JwUSiPcFlHrNLWJyAZDKK&fid=0x0:0x79a44c577165f939"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Island Bwoy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8HOxwMOkQ2N-9KvUsdJvNP39TlyKb7bS9M5EHzYJOvvKxzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The place had friendly and lively staff, tasty food and decent portion sizes. I would definitely come back here again. Only feedback I would give is to make sure you update prices on your menu as I was charged more than listed prices for takeout. Overall, the food was flavorful and authentic Jamaican cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyHFSnMW1rIkDIlgBH0WJ8D0Xw-0zs_53fIDz7&fid=0x0:0x79a44c577165f939"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Sue Suh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2nTtbDS0xCdS3kuMushxldxDpU89Bk6U50jQf-_LkIGKnOvs42g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing dinner yesterday! We love Jamaican food but never had a chance to visit one since we moved to Vancouver. This place met all our expectations. I absolutely loved their chili sauce as well 💕 So spicy!! Highly recommended :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO55b-5HmK4FP5EqI-kFI8pKOmcCAdhpMLhZjnI&fid=0x0:0x79a44c577165f939"],"When":"2022-2-14"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Can’t speak to the authenticity of the food, but it was fun to try a new cuisine. The restaurant has great atmosphere and a cool tiki bar. Seems like there was only one person running it when we went around 5pm on a weekday; service was quite slow even though we were the first and only ones in the restaurant. The server (owner?) was very friendly. My friend really loved the food here, I thought it was okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0pj3KyfwekpdetAXn0TEDbGO6CenlxiClbVlv&fid=0x0:0x79a44c577165f939"],"When":"2023-9-29"},{"Name":"Agni K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkDG9ralu9RS3nZ0v4vIcP6bNgjmOEKH-8N8DikYFi0AF_Esan=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Whether you are used to Jamaican cuisine or are brand new to it and would love to try it, look no further. This cosy restaurant will bring you the best Island vibes and will serve you authentic Jamaican food you’ll ever try. There’s a few free parking spots available right outside, convenient for a take-out order collection, and if you’re dining in, it’s easy to park and dine in.

Service: we were greeted by a warm reception from a lovely gentleman at the bar. We got to choose a table to our preference and were served with warmth and smiles, like a typical Jamaican welcome is known for. Our drinks were served promptly (had a glass of Pinot Grigio and a fruit punch). The fruit punch was created from scratch and fresh. Our host was thoroughly informative on portions and advised what to expect in each dish we picked out.

Food: we ordered 2 spicy beef patties (which Jamaica is known for famously), and they were so tasty! Freshly baked in the oven, crisp pastry and well seasoned beef filling, patties were served with their own homemade scotch bonnet pepper  sauce. It is very hot, so dip sparingly! For mains we ordered oxtail and curry goat. Oh goodness gracious, what an experience that was! The blend of flavours in both meats were superb! Accompaniments were rice ‘n’ peas (black beans, as authentic to Caribbean rice and peas style), steamed cabbage (with just enough crunch and flavour in them), and a quarter of shallow fried plantain. Each meat dish was decadent, succulent, fall off the bone yet juicy. With each bite, left us wanting more! We’ve had authentic Jamaican and other Caribbean cuisine before, in the Caribbean itself, and this food was just as you would be served in the islands. I would and will go again anytime I am in white rock, without a doubt!

Pro-tip: so, we loved our beef patties so much that we ordered a dozen to take home with us! The host gave us very clear instructions on getting them right in the oven. We tried at home and they were wonderful! I would highly recommend getting a box to take with you.

Pricing: Under $100 for 2 incl.dozen patties + drinks","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPI9HynpFpdLao1eIMWIxx0N6ovlQs-u5d4ddqO&fid=0x0:0x79a44c577165f939"],"When":"2024-1-19"},{"Name":"K Black","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWS9uLKAzshO9wERfuxPqbPOzBrU7bQLNeu-m5LeRcaHwPiZcQjdA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really happy to have found some food that reminds me of my old home. Food is really good and plentiful. Very casual and comfortable atmosphere. Everything was perfect..the only improvement that could take things to another level is if they cooked food - yam, coco, boiled dumpling. [{"Name":"Obianuju Moriah Esenwa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjgtByQCl8IoT57NPGFeANylTaYbdry8o12k5G5YwTM-8EN4w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tens all across the board! Best Vietnamese restaurant in white rock very homey atmosphere and delicious food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHNUW2m-4nwgqk2zlpyRSdFpAz34wHnyJYgQ0h&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Yuki Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgPmyvA2BNqgUzNUpeq8PkwjRislBWVbWQ9MeOGPDSzARy97eC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place have the nice and delicious PHO.  Their Vietnamese coffee also tasty which I really really loved.  This is my 2nd times to this restaurant, and each visit I will order their coffee.  Their soup broth is flavourful with beef taste.  Portion is good for the price.

Restaurant is not crowded most of the time.  Even the restaurant is not  busy, you have to wait at least 5 mins for server to come and take your order.  Parking is not convenient at all.  You have to park somewhere else and need some  walking distance to the restaurant. 2 hours free street parking in the area is available but hard to get a spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6_Mvcazo1VixOPrA8-8_ISpjZgMZvUP1ARMNx&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2024-5-10"},{"Name":"Kiet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIes8gRaxCDv8sgSVvXGiTrhSANpYnxpEK80yLm2KsGGUYiag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came with the family for dinner. Second time here. First time was somewhat busy and this time was the same. However, we were seated right away and did not have to wait. Lots of people in and out, as well as, a bunch of take out orders. Even with everything going on, I was surprised how quickly our food arrived. Must have been less than 10 mins after we ordered. Our order was not small either - 5 dishes for the four of us.

We ordered #40 seafood with rice noodle in soup, #44 egg noodle beef stew, #5 chicken wings, #2 pork spring rolls, #62 grilled lemongrass chicken and pork chop on rice. The wife had the beef stew and I had the rice dish. She was pleasantly surprised with the beef stew dish. For context, she always orders either the beef stew or the bun bo hue. The bun bo hue did not do much for her last time, but the stew she was a fan of. The soup was tasty and the beef tender. For me, I liked both the house special I had the first time and the rice dish I had this time. The meat was tender and flavorful, but would have liked the pork chop to be a bit more charred like the chicken was. Both the chicken and pork chop were cooked well. The rice was on the harder side though and would of been helped with more fish sauce.

I'm giving 4 stars for food since the seafood noodle soup dish and the bun bo hue were kind of bland and looked nothing like the picture in the menu. My guess is special dishes arent ordered as much and thats why they aren't as good. Regardless, they weren't bad, but looked kind of sad since we were expecting a bit more variety. The seafood content was lacking compared to other places we've been at. Seemed like it was loaded with more imitation crab than anything else.

Both the chicken wings and the spring rolls were spot on. Lots of flavor and cooked perfectly and not overly salty. They did seem crisper than usual though - maybe too long in the fryer. The spring rolls had a ton of taste and left me wanting more - I would be happy just eating spring rolls all day long.

All in all, this place exceeded our expectations. The food tasted great and wasn't overly salty or sweet (a common thing I am finding in South Surrey). Service was excellent with little to no wait and the portion sizes weren't small that's for sure. But, like every where else, prices are up across the board. On the plus side, it's always a good sign when the wife brings home the take out menu. Will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXNnFPMTPruOcDikuduobIHR42YvHRtNezPY-U&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2024-1-22"},{"Name":"Eli D.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLVehZaCki3TC6GcyJmDr7Wgh9MoZgACCVQfzP-Iv2zYNcg3Xx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pho 777 is always excellent! The food is consistently fresh and flavorful, and the service is quick and efficient. The owner is super nice and adds a personal touch to the experience.

If you’re craving delicious pho and reliable service, this is the place to go. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Than Paderog","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlEroTEpc5Shyb2XkmXkrKtJ0Ft6ijs_6eXRiUQnPr731YaraV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food. There is also ice cream here. Would recommend going here ☺️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOnrZwbRxUf9rDNHqH4g6P1-g2plpWphVOMbfi&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Ruth TC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5BmbSqaz-a6xEQ8H-IYF9xE6nis0xJokL2FIlUEJMw5DCop1iYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came for lunch after catching crabs at White Rock Pier. We ordered a grilled chicken + spring rolls cold vermicelli and a beef+tendons+tripe rice noodle soup. The former came in a huge bowl, with the best spring rolls I have had, freshly fried. While the latter had the beef tendons braised thoroughly. The waitress was very polite and courteous, worth supporting!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRvpTiB9eQRc6wqESIRfCzSkIYCmwB0KzCcHZy&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Andy Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDdEZRDU1NBOEQa2QncJ9Wz3jndRg-W2FgZzzXNwhHc95UZnqQKg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food at great prices, I go there for lunch almost everyday now. The Pork Banh Mi is delicious I’ve had it everyday for almost a week and still not sick of it. The Pho is delicious, the Bun Bo Hue is delicious just go, everything is good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYFIw2UEMfksTSRmjQ8N0pvzxtKcUENuTd55ua&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2024-6-15"},{"Name":"Sherrey Alindogan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWp7pl-DCu3BblLZAXhTwV3y_p_n2kCWqibkOcJdmfgtoUKhXG0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"[Updated]: Pho 777 is now our go-to and fave spot for Vietnamese food in White Rock! We’ve tried a few things of the menu and all were delicious! The broth of the pho isn’t as rich as some of the other phos I’ve had, but it does come with a lot of noodles and meat/toppings (aka worth your money). Would also recommend the deep fried calamari rings and spring rolls for appy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMUrBN0_KAu3cujNYC0SaodAyE8cXOWo1_jbS93&fid=0x0:0x532543d844fced31"],"When":"2022-11-15"}]

[{"Name":"Don Q","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJnQSmUDlDu6wqjfhXwrr9al_bZQlAPWWyB8XiXrDjvO4cmEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Al Capone & the Roma pizzas were amazing. Fresh ingredients & cooked to perfection. Thanks to the great staff. Although we live outside the deliver area…It was worth the drive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMS595B32tgsc6ox6AkoUR-iRRM6ok1twyXtytX&fid=0x0:0x4f108a6e113a804a"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Kevin Zahar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKU_AzJkjrDgG6UbFnM94nn-B5IX0Ul_TwF_Y1IbL2nUG9GG75s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We picked this pizza spot at random on a spontaneous drive through White Rock today.  We arrived just as they opened and the owners and staff were very kind and welcoming.   There are a few tables for dining out front, so limited seating, making this spot mainly a pick up/takeout location.  Worth it!  We waited 20 minutes for our pizza, which was very reasonable.  The dough was handmade, the ingredients/toppings were also fresh and visually pleasing.  Very good flavour for the dough, thin and no flop, great crispness.  Just a great pizza all around.  I highly recommend this location.  We thoroughly enjoyed it and will definitely stop in again next time we are in the area.
Thank to the staff and to the chef.

Well done! 👏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNZCLEMSJdlzf03CaduJ-_CK2Q3QgBZiwR1Lv9w&fid=0x0:0x4f108a6e113a804a"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"C. Pine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKsUAp97jIkJXe28_BBxwezAr9LRqfJ0RuRLRcJBtXl7qjefEsvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This is NOT Sicilian.  No.  What a disappointment.  What a waste of a drive.  Ordered Hawaiian and Spicy Sausage.  It was so bland.  The crust was thin and slightly crispy.  Service was friendly, but the food was a flop right down to the sauces.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6d613HokaLZrg7YZMnMs0ON8na4z18X-UwxB4&fid=0x0:0x4f108a6e113a804a"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Enrique Yep","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVquIpskP4Ca-Y03KLwCPd4uD6-mpdn9C3JAbeInjQLrHNRnuB10g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a good experience, and the pizza was superb.  Tasty, thin crust pizza with flavour from fresh ingredients.   Only downside was that I made an order earlier in the day for 4:30, but when I arrived, they were behind 15 minutes.   Yes, I know it was a busy Halloween night,  but it was a small inconvenience.   Overall,  highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Stauffer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_DRJK4pUg7pVKjay99XKneVmceX2vBcROZ8Rs1Re8pfvmvJ8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"When they’re good, they’re great...
But as a few people have mentioned, when the old guy is in, the pizza is great.  Tonight, well… he wasn’t in…

On a good day, each bite is so delicious at so many different levels - “A potpourri of flavour”

Tonight, burnt on the bottom, undercooked on top and I went back to tell them I really wasn’t impressed.  I got “that’s how we cook our pizzas”.  NOPE, I don’t buy that line. That maybe is how you cook your pizzas when the old guy isn’t around, but why is that!  I wonder if the oven isn’t cleaned properly or the younger staff don’t know how to manage the temperature of the oven… really don’t care - fix it.

This is how good companies fail. I really don’t want you to fail.  I want to have that amazing pizza every single time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1Qc628EG61myrI9u0F1Pq_f_Dk2puUUms-Z0m&fid=0x0:0x4f108a6e113a804a"],"When":"2023-7-6"},{"Name":"Jen S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6yRDu3X2tYRf22dSS2L1HUQ_---VPNFSZyVWrJW6KXuGpfNIHww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The word on the street is that this is the best pizza in White Rock. I don’t know why I’ve waited so long to try it - I’ve been missing out! Got the Very Veggie thin crust pizza and it was loaded with all kinds of veggies, even butternut squash. The corners of the crust were drizzled with something sweet, probably honey. It was delicious! I’m excited to try the other veggie and seafood pizzas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPl3b4J45lJol0JQt4lX9ZLL1j2K7j8gmLywypo&fid=0x0:0x4f108a6e113a804a"],"When":"2023-3-12"},{"Name":"canadiantoycollector","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8uAVaVf4LAjfRa7o-VuIM9KweWqVeEd8_LNAEezp5aMr8BA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ordered through Uber for the calzone (pep) 2 for 1 deal. Very bland and unfortunately not so tasty, could use some seasoning like oregano or basil, tastes like generic Mozzarella and pepperoni as well, size was good, nothing special about the dough. Also I find it extremely unreasonable you do not get at least one 2 Oz dip even house made marinara, you have to pay 1.75 for a 2 Oz cup. I wanted to support local shop, but literally the pizza hut melts are far tastier in my opinion and less expensive. Unfortunately will do be dining here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gillian Gardner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3BmBUflBwDqh4s0UghWS9W6l5VcdvUgFgvodm2ISzf9cao2Vw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had the Tuscan chicken pizza today and it was the best thing I’ve ever tasted.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRj7cSErfvZ2XoZHi9LgbTojl0s1qfbKGQKPgd&fid=0x0:0x4f108a6e113a804a"],"When":"2024-12-10"}]

Zero flavour in the two mains.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNerBoFmSLbV3wizcCKEW0qhgTzfIlsr3Y16U3T&fid=0x0:0x723a10b3e297c7d0"],"When":"2024-11-28"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fun brunch date with a friend with yummy food! We had a great time with nice patio seating.

We got the Chilaquiles ($22), Zapo Skillet ($22) and Ceviche de Atun ($23). All had great flavours but I think we could’ve ordered a bigger variety of dishes as they all seemed to mix in with each. The ceviche was my favourite - super fresh and paired really well with the homemade chips.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtB9c-Wyl293Ftluo4Mupziz5LJtlzzHkpZOo6&fid=0x0:0x723a10b3e297c7d0"],"When":"2024-6-19"},{"Name":"jackie spears","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQSpIRsoeLZKzPhRjMQrTuHhWXI2eeJUv_G6fSe8jGwzpSrvc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely absolutely incredible and delicious food. Highly highly recommend this restaurant for authentic,genuine right off the local markets of Mexico!!! Jajajaja!!! Right along the strip in beautiful white rock right at the beach can't get any better! Definitely try the chicken tacos or fish tacos but make sure that if you order the fish tacos you get the Chipotle mayo on the side just sayin 😜🔥 lol
Our server Unis was a delight and if you get her as your server she'll take care of you 👌🏻
Viva Mexico 🇲🇽🌮🌯🇲🇽","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgTq4M9xe7By70Fxs6Jni4iY3Mai83I2UMNGDP&fid=0x0:0x723a10b3e297c7d0"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Clayton C.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUghLXFcVk4XWHNjXn_4E9cz-LD_dYTgAgtVHaLSobKYpYW4DunVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"🌮✨ Just had another great meal at Zapoteca! This place is a solid 4-star gem in South Surrey/White Rock. The food? Absolutely divine! 😋 Authentic flavors that transport you straight to Mexico. My top picks? The Molcajetes del Mar, Enchiladas, and Sofrito de Mariscos – all bursting with fresh, delicious seafood. 🍤

The main downside – the service can be a bit of a letdown. Every visit, it’s the same story: slow, inattentive, and sometimes you feel like a magician trying to get a drink refill. Pro tip: order two drinks at once to save yourself the hassle! Haha

Despite the service hiccups, Zapoteca remains a go-to spot for the best Mexican cuisine in the area. If you haven’t been, you’re seriously missing out! 🌟","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDY2Cv5JsOEfQ801GME0iiv0NPOhk71eK2ft0q&fid=0x0:0x723a10b3e297c7d0"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Yang Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBcibpksoiQktvsA27s30xwhYuleD4a6Xt8BC367VmNsJPiuP7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The fish taco was amazing here! Overall food was good and happy hour starts at 2pm!! They also have a fully covered patio with plenty of seatings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxj6aFNnudcDBYGQTVvOLCMP7n6NYWYJtXXgkI&fid=0x0:0x723a10b3e297c7d0"],"When":"2024-5-17"}]

Their salted pepper chicken wings was definitely a must order here as the wings are crispy and soaked with their spices on top. The lemongrass pork with rice is another highlight here as the meat was charred perfectly along with some tasty veggies on the side. The vermicelli was excellent as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9Zw_dP2Ehyjy49xeFiXQVpSwTWmus4c0KhotR\u0026fid=0x0:0xd10ec06237fcc7de"],"When":"2023-12-13"},{"Name":"Lorna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMRkfvPpY4aQamfTxPu9_oR_LcV5akdo_DheKroIrJe6ksQHcR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Finished off a morning walk near by and Mommy was wanting some Vietnamese food. This place had good ratings so we thought to give it a try. Flavours were pretty mild for us but the restaurant was clean and service was friendly. Food does come out pretty slow even though the restaurant wasn’t even busy. Prices are cheap. Would recommend if you’re craving Vietnamese food in the white rock area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJI2NmpXJmziaqpAiGSh393uKTW9UYrq-b1a9O\u0026fid=0x0:0xd10ec06237fcc7de"],"When":"2022-10-8"},{"Name":"Jordan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnKPvBzEtCXZqNtKEAvfwxKMW2R9rs5XBWBmRMN3qb8k85bG4Z2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As soon as we walked in here the server was so sweet and friendly. We'll come back here next time we visit White Rock 🙏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3qfY7HGMn3Qi4FFdaPF7mbwhB2jzZsEIWZwhg\u0026fid=0x0:0xd10ec06237fcc7de"],"When":"2023-7-1"},{"Name":"David","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIaRYwtE6eWHbrzYJXgA4SL-J2Y8zGC4l9UxeU2XYBRSbS8bw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Have not been here in a year or so. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Terry Zlot","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5jZdQ7VgZvHJtYd06aEUnmlmexCY12vLke1GW7Qe2YPt6FdoE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hosted a private family event at Onyx for 16 people and they absolutely blew us away! Nicholas was great to deal with and went above and beyond to accommodate. Our server Katja was wonderful and made sure everyone was happy including the kids, and the food was excellent. Perfect steaks, great house wine, unbelievable creme brulee - everything was fantastic. Thanks for a wonderful evening!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPlt_937euAy9wDsdqyWLq4wWmaIG1F5qaFNvTo&fid=0x0:0x4bfa4573feabb28e"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Megs Darcy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMhq7KKmmqdJpMYnd0Ul12-HZD8SzBVoVb0bN4VfCkVK0gegMR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a fantastic date night. First time we have been and the food was amazing (bone in ribeye, Gorgonzola mashed potatoes, Brussels in honey,). All were cooked to perfection and we loved their a la cartel steak menu so we could personalize our experience.
My husband adored the prawn appetizer and stuffed garlic bread (think delicious mini parcels of flavour) along with his smoked old fashioned.
The service was excellent so much that we realized what poor service we were getting other places - attentive but not overwhelming.
Highly recommend we will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZInKSaZ3sMqs6Vu-lcpWfr9a0z-jcgh_ueHNY&fid=0x0:0x4bfa4573feabb28e"],"When":"2024-2-24"},{"Name":"Lisa Zarin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKmuIqAiVmU0eIAErO7B_IT3aJb0l6poSYs3zD0ijHw_S00=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hosted our annual company Christmas Party this year at ONYX Steakhouse.  To say we were impressed is an understatement.  Nicholas and team blew us away with their attention to detail, guiding us along the way from planning to executing our evening.  Our staff raved about the evening, from the food and drinks, to the atmosphere in the private dining room.  During the evening, Nick and his team went above and beyond making sure we had everything we needed to ensure our work family had an amazing evening.  Would highly recommend ONYX Steakhouse to anyone.  You won't be disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIygaDSSO61NcNIbud4s6Uj0PbtgQo0vaG_qf6U3HgvVNx6MA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Took my family here for dinner. 8 of us in total. From the time I sat down until the time I had my drink in my hand was 30 min. Maybe two other tables in the restaurant at the time. We went on a Sunday where they do a prime rib..... they want you to pre order the prime rib if you are interested. We pre ordered 3 prime rib done anywhere from medium rare to medium, all the prime rib came out well done. Waiter was nice, restaurant was clean. When you are charging the prices you are charging, gotta be better.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Silveria Redato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2yVDQzqDRhjvSPVjjWJvNdnV6ENr95oieBl4Nyi-O-3KTvA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Made last minute reservations here last night for my friends bday dinner. They were more than happy to accommodate us.
This was my first time visiting this restaurant so I wasn’t entirely sure what to expect.
The food was perfection. Everything from the food quality, atmosphere , service and knowledgeable staff was 💯.
Our server made very good wine and food recommendations and was able to answer all our questions regarding the menu.
I’ve been to a lot of steakhouses and I would have to say this is one of my favourites in the lower mainland.
Thanks for having us! We’ll definitely be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rita Hunter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEaj7axYmjQk4VOQmdrs4PGWgtbetnLoV6RgAhtOUKzCX7xA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere was lovely in that we could have conversation without having to shout above the music.
Our meals were delicious! We had the short rib and the yellowfin tuna…. Both done to perfection!
Also the Caesar salad was wonderful! We also had the foraged mushrooms (I question if they’re actually foraged but nonetheless very tasty)
Nate was our server …. Very pleasant and contributed to our very “real” experience with his conversation and personality!!
We recommend onyx for your special occasion!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marek Lewis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZGnVGWctUS4PHrbPJiUsL5BQNqjCok7pCYnPod2N66TMgeRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent food, excellent service, outstanding atmosphere! I started off my meal with the arancini appetizer, every bite was a burst of flavor and texture. The crispy exterior gave way to a creamy and savory center, showcasing the chef's attention to detail and skill in crafting each dish. For the main course, the prawn linguine was a true masterpiece that left a rich and lasting impression. Each component of the dish was expertly prepared, highlighting the quality of ingredients and the expertise of the kitchen staff. I highly recommend Onyx Steakhouse to anyone whether they're coming in for a special occasion or simply craving a memorable meal.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Максим Рубинов","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbGdNhSlxoyvJdFaQUOslZIwvqD8N2b5VPhXGydw7UbgkVL2Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Perfect service and nice atmosphere. Good place actually, with rich bar and else. But(!) it’s a steak house at the first, and steak wasn’t good. I was hangry and ate it, but it was worse as cheapest steak from place like “Denny’s”. I ordered delmonico in medium-rare. And it was overcooked, plus I don’t sure, that it was “40/50-day-aged Angus Signature Reserve beef gold AAA+”, as they say in their menu and website.
Manager Katya was very kind. In the end, I think they should change one of this thing: Chef or meat or price.
P.S. on the picture I show you most fat and rare part of steak","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPu8u7C9MYLmmmD_GEWCLeeY1m-sLMmOtR4ft2Z&fid=0x0:0x4bfa4573feabb28e"],"When":"2024-5-4"}]

[{"Name":"Lila Cao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD5E5q90-uLgMp-kP3rrqS_FNXybXltvOPpf2biARtm36fnNM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Family style Japanese restaurant which reminded me the small bistros in Japan when we travelled there. The sashimi is very fresh, the teriyaki series are well seasoned and served hot. The service is superb, all staff are kind and considerable. Will definitely come back again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOY86Z9iSdOqKdSWOfcT-UZatSe44rAEJB_R5Zi&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"JB CHU","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgWSLLs0R--vY6HThjK4A_oQpcCL09XMjbjMMjW_zVqw3j73-u=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the best place for sushi with a good price range. Fish was fresh and the service was wonderful with great selection of menu. My favorites were the Aburi set, along with the Shabu Soup and Prawns Tempura. The restaurant is always booked. Best to make reservations way in advance or show up right before they open.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN0pvvHu1I75REOh-wahOICVqzakGtlqMn6eyj&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2019-2-8"},{"Name":"Chris Schlichter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXP2nmbFeRizY3HwQkiGgtoKaxdsHqkj_YWk316XadIX-oY0axEGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What an amazing experience. The out side does not accurately depict what you will get inside. If you live in South Surrey or White Rock call them up and make a reservation. The service is great just a little slow, but food this good takes time so just relax and enjoy the time with family and friends. We didn't have a bad dish. Some of the best tempura I have had anywhere in Metro Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJlSlk0g6VJoTMJErOUMLPxbL1XzYPjatfNpXa&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2018-6-1"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you've been to White Rock and have never had Kappa, you are truly missing out. Quality food made by the sweetest Japanese couple. I've been eating here for over 10 years and it never disappoints. My favourite sushi in all of metro Vancouver. My favourites: dynamite roll, lotus root tempura, sunomono, flounder fringe and tamago nigiri. We have never ordered Kappa and not gotten the tamago, it is THE best. The operating hours are Thursday to Saturday, dinner only - make sure to plan ahead!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjysGeA2bsa2FmEKz-8LSrKnw7EaTK6Dgz8sI9&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2022-4-26"},{"Name":"Kabbi卡比","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWReAxdrQzl-FEUdWuw6Aywow5YG0442FERdAfbH3RPIulm5F6P=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If someone asks me how good Kappa is, I would simply tell them that it is better than Taka.

The taste, the service, and the environment is GREAT. There is really nothing I can complain about.

However, this is a family ran restaurant, and the owners are getting aged. They now only open 3 days a week. I can still remember the days they open 4-5 days a week.

Also the food here is normally a bit pricy. Two people can easily spend 100$ here, so if you are looking for cheap sushi, then this is not the place you want to go. But if you are looking for high quality aburi/nigini sushi, then you should definitely come here.

The restaurant has been opened for over 35 years in White Rock, BC, and I would say it is one of the best sushi restaurants in lower mainland.

Wish the owners stay healthy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgvpToCsHFI2PyYOauoCLhpUiQIFY7LqW_S9zL&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2019-10-12"},{"Name":"Emi Hg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZ3WVbWeTftJ4V_eLfqJw4qf-J1Ywh5R593pMBgu_spHg5sA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their tuna tataki and beef sashimi are so fresh and on point. Not big fan of teriyaki dish.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNmlo6QwdOJ3lmgUtq732gV82U2PORslLGSmaC&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2024-3-2"},{"Name":"Food Critic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxCV4ZgVG_R5ONa7sxFGrIgfCjX6QoSBwh2y5YwIbzRDSdZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Overview: A truly authentic Japanese dining experience, a mom and pop run Japanese eatery. They are based from Nagoya. You must take off your shoes to seat yourself to eat. Each table is sectioned off in quarters enclosed with the curtains so it feels like you are having a private dinner with your group or dinner date. Truly one of a kind of a restaurant; a must try for all. The experience is worth the price. Definitely not a place to come when you are hungry, but perfect for a fine-dining experience.

Vibe: Great authentic vibe, the minute we walked in, we were welcomed by courteous staff. We truly felt like we were back in Japan.

Flavour: Truly amazing flavours we haven’t had elsewhere. The prawn gyoza came in 5 at the price of $9. Each gyoza had one full prawn in tact with the tail, and was extremely flavourful wrapped in a pork filling inside. Accompanying it was a slightly sweet and tart vinegar based sauce. Chef's Assorted Sashimi ($40) was definitely a smaller portion, but very freshly sourced sashimi, and the star of that order was the prawn sashimi (extremely buttery and sweet). White Rock Roll was extremely flavourful, not only because it had lots of filling, but the seaweed used was of a high quality and the flavour really worked well with the filling. Also, although the roll was massive, none of the ingredients fell to pieces as you picked up a piece of the roll, and this speaks to the chef’s attention to detail.

Originality: Gyozas were extraordinary, first time I’ve seen them with tails at the end, but retains moisture and juiciness. "Gyo Za" soup, you can tell it was freshly made to order, with a swirled egg added and one gyoza in the soup (small portion for 1 only).

Service: Extremely courteous staff, kind and thoughtful. Provided complimentary Gomae while we waited for our food. Food came out in order, with appetizers to start, and allowed time in between to allow guests to fully enjoy the experience. The mains came shortly after.

Overall Experience/Star of the Show: Prawn Gyoza and Whiterock Roll.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMlxwXh7gpJ1OJ3ciL-FC2rwnlWIYybKTDHyjkp&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2019-9-10"},{"Name":"Darryn Kar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdGNilEUkcW7nP2qRJRgYVXsTqIq7xXPT3AZrLOJ53NlbgoSDg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Small traditional style Japanese restaurant, offers great service and a selection of fresh fish. Reservations are mandatory as there aren't a lot of seats. Counted 5 groups of people going to get in without reservations and "booked for the night" was the answer every time. Must try the aburi and a selection of the nigiri. Added bonus, dinner courses come with dessert","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJzaKf1dVw3DIUAnPesinN_oRpbnMZ9cTDL38C&fid=0x0:0x65530ccece6cd8b0"],"When":"2018-7-28"}]

[{"Name":"Foodieatlarge Ou812!","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV5WjUsogcvFcdpk650G44_1nDSsUxfDfJjUXorbWVcHcaIaXI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Return visit after 30 years.
Superb location,gr8 views.
Clean establishment.
Comfortable breezy dining rooms.
Let's review what I loved :
Superb pita,warm, fluffy and flavourful.Perfectly cooked pilaf seasoned well. The potatoes were the best I've enjoyed to date. Bright lemony notes that melt in ur mouth with starchy fluffiness. Literally. Mmm,mmm.
House de-caff was excellent, strong & fresh.
The chicken was properly seasoned, tender and moist.
Chicken was a bounty  of classic Mediterranean flavours.
The Lamb, however,
was nearly unidentifiable lacking aroma of that savoury lamb gamey-ness lamb offers. Almost had a mild near beef flavour rather than Lamb. My lamb totally lacked authentic Mediterranean notes whatsoever.
The lamb mouth feel was tender but void of proper seasoning imo ???
Idk?
The bland Becamel on my garnish was scant and absent of flavour. Garnish also needed 90 seconds more cooking to be digestible imo.
Greek salad needed a splash of acid to wake up the taste buds. Some fragrant  oregano, some olive oil and  balanced ratios of cuke, onion and  green pepper would be an improvement  cos our salads were riddled with less than fresh cukecumbers, and hardly any green peppers.
Service was friendly, didn't  touch our drinking glass rims once ( the sign of a true seasoned pro ) and maintained a warm genuine banter. She missed the boat by checking back 15 mins after serving our entrees. This is futile and made us feel neglected. Js.

Appy Trails kids,
Brianm
Foodieatlarge.OU812 on Google maps

Back catalogue visit Foodieatlarge.yelp.ca","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV1p5mtfDN0a6vblkQkvYyHb9Tq1PDbwZjKA6B&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Delphine Zhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnXhPhZs7zo-3zqBHxLhkO4iXyM_xsNyE4WXxy15x9mYexkW-X=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our Sunday dinner. Not so crowded. It seems people came to celebrate. During our dinner, there were three birthday singing...lol. I ordered seafood kebabs and my friend ordered lamb kebabs. They came with a bowl of salad, some veggies on the side, and a good amount of rice. Good quality materials, good cooking, good taste and good service. Price is very reasonable. Very satisfied. Will go back again soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyJbVzjxaabi7k03pUk7OvRHHQ0ZVm4HA8XDMk&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Barry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKc6DQEnz6T22PQ5Sil1VwuHDjO87yudfKagQKkZG-Kh3f1ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent meal out at this Greek restaurant in White rock. Never disappoints gluten-free is available, just check in with your server, etc. upon arrival.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9KO8jWnXp7RKW4X8qNb78vYzuIoXk4qDAuasA&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2024-9-11"},{"Name":"Glenn Atchison","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_QHFJJwsUlADYVeRuvKypI2P8Z-MsK04lXLPol8NByqoYJg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Unbelievable experience. The place was packed but was still very comfortable. Joyous music and entertainment and dancing and everyone having so much fun! Can't forget about the plate smashing which is a Greek thing!  Food was unbelievable. Served hot, fresh, with excellent service. Staff is exceptionally friendly and does not hurry you alone. Take your time, enjoy the place, have fun. Reservations are pretty well a must as this place is always busy, but that should tell you how good the food and the service is.  Be aware that parking in White Rock is metered till midnight and on a busy night it can be difficult to find a parking spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOS_vJOrqcv1ath6f8l-Il-88KHILUuv_jIr6nN&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2024-3-18"},{"Name":"Summer Yandon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaVVX9rmZ1eU7NrzoAzZ1WMDMgbnNzQuIW-WyCpZixy9wdO-X_hA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This greek restaurant was not only had amazing staff, food and atmosphere but also a beautiful view. The servings were large and delicious! Highly recommended!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPq4TFPp7DejZe8MWCo2Al0YnOrUrNXOsOaw1NJ&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2024-6-1"},{"Name":"Michelle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKX4ilARjrlnPqJwrQ9suKEqJ9KDG80hq4x6niDvzVfY60h3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered the Calamari dinner and the first photo is what I was served. The Greek salad was warm and the tomato’s were mealy, as if they had sat under a warmer. The calamari was soggy, moist and flavourless. I am not the type to say anything but the server happened to come by as I was trying to pick through the calamari and I let her know how bad it was. She said she would get me a new batch of calamari right away. She brought new calamari and it was fresh at least, but it still was so flavourless and I left most of it (as you can see in my second photo). The rice was over cooked, and the only thing I didn’t totally hate was the potatoes. This was probably the worst Greek food I’ve ever had in my life, and I am a total foodie and love trying new places. This place was packed and I truly didn’t understand and why. $34 for a plate of unseasoned mush. Save your money and go to any other Greek Restaurant in the lower mainland.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSR1KrxdKtXKKvWKcTAhAHnHvSr1sJBJVaDOYS&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2023-5-22"},{"Name":"Alexandra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWod6EbW5D4lQiIr-KZpM7_XafS1GjbPyWk8hXBh63OaLnzfHCWEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went there yesterday for a belated birthday celebration for my friend. Susan, our server, was absolutely phenomenal. Friendly, professional, personable and easy to talk to as we were getting seated and ready to order. She was attentive and on top of things, throughout our entire meal, coming to check on us, refill waters, even though we were the only table outside on the patio, she didn't forget about us for one second. The patio was also amazing, the weather was great and had a lovely beach view.

The gesture from Susan that made the experience exceptional was that as she was collecting our dishes overheard our conversation about my friend's birthday which was last week. She generously offered to bring us a slice of cake and sang my friend happy birthday. Thank you Susan!!

Towards the end of our meal, we also interacted with the hostess, Georgia, she was a gem as well. The food and service was amazing.

As for their food love love love their vegetarian moussaka 😍 bit on the pricey side so it's better for more celebratory occasions or treating yourself once in a while meals but their food is very delicious! Every single time!

Can get a bit busy sometimes, esp during nicer summer days on the weekends but good if you're able to avoid those. Forgot some pita once from a doordash order during dinner rush but was able to get credit for it as soon as we realized something was missing and called.

Love any excuse to order or dine at Cosmos 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQli0ztCYwl3jB1kiis1vaVv5Sv6NqZkESHYUf&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2022-8-2"},{"Name":"henry lo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYQpQrlrCMMz950b2rs1RJvk42Xhtblpc6h8kmr87h5z3Avw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a date night with my partner there. The 3 courses meal of $37 is quite reasonable for the quality and quantity of the food being served.

The Escargot was slightly disappointing but again this is a Greek restaurant and not a French place so it's alright.

The dessert was quite good but a bit overly sweet for my taste. I do recommend trying out this place if you visit Whiterock!

However, note that the restaurant is quite busy and you might have to wait awhile :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMljbUdbTETjJaGp6o0AC6XaHwL-N7fnuHmOLMS&fid=0x0:0xb376af80d8076a4c"],"When":"2021-7-27"}]

Loved both the items. Would definitely recommend. Service was good. And it would be great family dining place. Had great clean washrooms too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPrR1JgFChcJkNuXJUz7SBzZmF-V-tutjl21K-u&fid=0x0:0x20e604021e9fdd53"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Satwant Singh kamboj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSp3uwXFZEKpPz7NoHRZoUU3wP-Hk2z0EKrdZ_tTXMONccBPp-8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an amazing dining experience at India Chaat House & Restaurant, and I can’t say enough about their delicious 'fish pakora' and 'chicken tikka'...! The fish pakoras were crispy, perfectly seasoned, and melted in the mouth, while the chicken tikka was tender, smoky, and bursting with authentic flavors. Both dishes were simply outstanding and showcased the richness of Indian cuisine.

What made the visit even more memorable was the exceptional service from "Reet". She was attentive, friendly, and went above and beyond to ensure we had a fantastic experience. Her knowledge of the menu and her helpful recommendations added a personal touch that made the meal even more enjoyable. Reet’s warm hospitality truly set the tone for a perfect evening.

If you’re looking for flavorful Indian food and top-notch service, India Chaat House & Restaurant is the place to go. Highly Highly recommended, and I’ll definitely be back!
@Itzsatwantsingh@gmail.com

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Zoe Howkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGWa-lvF8s5H_-zVorHRwR65b65GTGbFVT9oKxWDIhPlh2lxOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My recent dining experience at the White Spot in White Rock, BC, was nothing short of extraordinary. From the moment I entered the establishment, I was immediately struck by the ambiance, which was a harmonious blend of modern elegance and understated sophistication. The lighting was artfully subdued, casting a warm and inviting glow over the immaculately clean and meticulously organized dining area. The seating arrangement was spacious, allowing for a sense of privacy and intimacy, while still maintaining the vibrant buzz of a well-frequented, bustling restaurant.

Upon being seated, I was promptly greeted by a staff member whose demeanor exuded professionalism and an unwavering commitment to exemplary service. Every interaction was polished and courteous, and it was clear that customer satisfaction was paramount. The waitstaff demonstrated an impeccable knowledge of the menu, offering insightful recommendations and showing an almost encyclopedic awareness of the dishes’ intricate ingredients and their potential pairings.

As for the culinary offerings, I was beyond impressed by the diversity and creativity embedded in the menu selections. I opted for the Legendary Burger 🍔, an iconic choice, which arrived as a culinary masterpiece, perfectly presented and meticulously crafted. The patty was succulent and flavorful, seasoned to perfection, and its texture was sublime, a delicate balance between tenderness and a satisfyingly slight crispiness on the edges. The amalgamation of fresh ingredients—lettuce, tomato, and their signature Triple O sauce—elevated the burger to new gastronomic heights. The flavor profile was both complex and well-rounded, offering a symphony of tastes that danced on the palate. The fries were nothing short of ethereal—crispy on the outside, soft and fluffy on the inside—delivering the perfect complement to the main course.

Throughout the dining experience, the atmosphere remained convivial yet serene, striking the perfect balance between lively and relaxing. I was particularly impressed by the timing of the service; each course was brought to the table with precision, neither rushed nor delayed, allowing for a thoroughly enjoyable and leisurely dining experience.

In summary, White Spot in White Rock, BC, surpassed all expectations in every conceivable way. The food was exceptional, the service was impeccable, and the ambiance was the epitome of refined comfort. I wholeheartedly recommend this establishment to anyone seeking a dining experience that transcends the ordinary and ventures into the realm of the truly sublime.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHPmcjo-swounHPvEkNvMfCt6rQBGokixoHJmu&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Joseph Fung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkZEb8e5c-d48CtQKYY357rxTS2qVXdqhij1aQG0wnJ9RdQaSW8g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A Hidden Gem in White Rock 🌟

This was my sister's family's second-to-last night in Vancouver, and after a tiring trip back from Seattle, we decided to stop by White Spot. We stumbled upon this location in White Rock, and what a gem it is! 💎

We walked in around 7:30 PM, and to our surprise, it wasn't crowded at all. The spacious seating and perfectly done decor immediately set the tone for a relaxing evening. We were greeted by a friendly staff member with a big smile 😊—a sign that we were in for a good time.

Despite not having much of an appetite, I let my 12-year-old niece order whatever she wanted while I opted for a kid's meal 🍔. My in-law chose the fish & chips 🐟🍟, my sister ordered a steak that was cooked to perfection 🥩, and my niece loved her teriyaki chicken bowl 🍜. I thoroughly enjoyed my kid's meal too—sometimes, simple is best!

The service was fantastic, likely because it was a quiet Monday night with everyone at home prepping for the week ahead. We had a great experience and a very enjoyable evening. Thank you, White Spot White Rock! 🙏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNv64FmpqrNYE4J_aceCfXKiT54IgE5IAvxR19C&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Jimmy Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW9P_PvAXPpRm-rqp7o8PSBXZMDOwFMGeyAtE9SD11GccOz3oU3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"An excellent breakfast experience, I really like the atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXsZ1NQ-mUa8ShlfW3mgvJ5FjqZnh70bqkbgk2&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2024-10-13"},{"Name":"G L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaj1T89qDIhuu6T5sVgXL4DtRbakWigD-JSOxFaKwb96Qnno59=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We came here for dinner on a Friday night around 7:30PM. The hostess sat us within 5 minutes. However it took the server some time to bring us waters. The restaurant was NOT full.

The food was really subpar and took forever. We ordered the steak and pasta. The steak was average, but the mashed potatoes was NOT seasoned at all. There was nothing to dip for the flavourless potatoes (they charge $3-$4 for a side gravy). The pasta was a bit bland, but nothing some extra chili + salt can’t fix (I couldn’t taste the wine sauces the the dish apparently had).

We ordered happy hour poutine. The fries were okay, and the gravy’s taste was good, but the cheese curds aren’t appropriately melted.

The server checked on us twice throughout the night: 1) after tasting our food - but took a while so we had to ask another server for chilis/other 2) when we finished our food - then proceeded to take 10-15min for our bill.

I don’t know this is just such a disappointment for a white spot experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLFp5XP0RnUTZO_41p2x9q9R0G8fDmq9uLP9oQ&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Tommy “Powerbuilderwannabe” Xiao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfDi4iFU0b7G0chKTplbE5u7vf20zgZVI66nBpazopRw9TLzij=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great restaurant and nice dining atmosphere as usual! The food quality remains consistent and delicious throughout time and staffs are extremely friendly. I enjoy their Big Denver Omelette a lot as the omelette was cooked perfectly with a side of fresh Sourdough Bread and Smashed salted potatoes. The Charred Tomato & Garlic Prawn Spaghetti was nice as well. The prawns was tender and the sauce for the spaghetti was refreshing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPe1L5XUVebWwzwMaJUj7TGnTnwv7voS2Zf-Ja&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2023-5-30"},{"Name":"Joey Tambanua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLg7nFQDq3FmBDRwCq0QfVTR4I1k5X2qUBoKwbsF_3XdW-16BuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Has a variety to pick from burgers to salads; they have alcohol beverages/ bar too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3KYeCRRHaLpJAVipn4J1fJ7dClDgPjHlxnhs9&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Helen Jordin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6v6IPAr1Gk_K3zmJ85RgLMvYID58PYn_1XxNSnsoqHd-_Gauk7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good is consistently good at White Spots. Service is variable, and this day we had a discontented hostess, (not welcoming, tossed the cutlery in a heap on the table), but a great waitress! Food was slow to come, but at least the server checked in on us regularly to reassure us that it was coming!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maaya Hayashi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIIWazMRfse7gJYCE3IHWKaz4frn0U3i6RE-VviDgjLK1NZDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"RAW CHICKEN BURGER

My brother in law ordered White Spot last night for dinner via Ubereats for our family and I ordered their Gochujang Fried Chicken burger with fries and coleslaw. I had about 3/4 of the burger until I realized that the thickest part of the chicken burger was fully raw inside. The burger was covered in a thick spicy sauce, so it was hard to notice how raw it was until I cut into it with a knife. White Spot is supposed to be a well established restaurant so we were all shocked at the rawness of the burger. I'm also heavily pregnant, so the risk of having uncooked/raw chicken is a huge risk to my baby and me. We immediately contacted White Spot, and the manager gave a $50 food credit via email for the "disappointing experience" with the "under done chicken" (an understatement...it was raw!!) which I think is ridiculous because firstly, why would we want to go back after this experience, and secondly, it's not even the entire bill or even a refund, but a food credit. It's one thing for a steak to be rare, or have raw fish like sushi, but chicken and pork cannot be eaten undercooked or raw. We're incredibly disappointed by the food and the way they handled the situation. I will be contacting Fraser Health as well as this is a serious issue.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7Rqr7-q6IrzYCG74ldnvQbTlJkG5LS4L2AAvD&fid=0x0:0xb4879ed74ce9246e"],"When":"2023-7-17"}]
